Product Name: CarSight
Problem Statement: CarSight helps inexperienced car buyers navigate the used car market by analyzing private seller listings and translating complex pricing and reliability information into simple, actionable insights.

MVP Goal: Build a working web-based listing analysis platform that can evaluate real vehicle listings and provide useful buying guidance.

Target Launch: Flexible / development begins immediately after PRD completion.

Target Users
Primary User Profile
Who
First-time car buyers
Inexperienced car shoppers
Users who know little about vehicle reliability or pricing
Buyers browsing private seller marketplaces like Facebook Marketplace or Craigslist
Their Main Problems
They don’t know if a car is reliable
They don’t know if the asking price is fair
There are too many vehicle options and trims
Listings are inconsistent and hard to interpret
They are afraid of overpaying or buying a problematic car
Current Solutions
Users currently:

browse private seller marketplaces manually
occasionally check Kelley Blue Book
ask friends/family for help
search random forums
mostly guess
User Persona Example
“Emily”
Emily is a college student looking for her first real car. She likes BMWs because they look sporty and luxurious, but she has no idea which models are reliable or expensive to maintain.

She browses private seller listings online but struggles to:

understand pricing
compare options
identify scams
know what issues to look for
She wants a simple tool that explains:
“Is this car actually a good idea?”

