MVP Features
1. Listing Analysis Engine
Description
Allows users to:

paste listings
upload screenshots
upload PDFs or Carfax reports
manually enter car information
Why Essential
This is the main entry point of the product.

2. Vehicle Valuation Engine
Description
Determines:

estimated market value
overpricing/underpricing
fair value range
Potentially using:

internal pricing algorithms
market comparison data
future external APIs
Why Essential
Users need fast answers to:
“Is this actually worth the asking price?”

3. Reliability + Risk Engine
Description
Analyzes:

known vehicle issues
engine/platform reliability
ownership risks
recalls
common failures
Outputs:

reliability score
ownership risk level
common issue summaries
Why Essential
Most inexperienced buyers do not understand long-term reliability differences between cars.

4. Confidence / Suspicion Rating
Description
Analyzes listing trustworthiness using:

unrealistic pricing
suspicious listing details
incomplete information
inconsistent data
Outputs:

confidence score
risk warnings
possible scam indicators
Why Essential
Helps protect inexperienced buyers from bad or suspicious listings.

5. Negotiation Assistant
Description
Provides:

suggested offers
talking points
negotiation leverage
issue-based questions to ask sellers
Example:
“This model commonly develops transmission issues around 100k miles. Ask whether this repair has already been completed.”

Why Essential
Helps users negotiate using real information rather than guessing.

